    <div class="inner-block">
      <section class="biography" id="biography">
        <h1 class="label">Biography</h1>
        <div class="govspeak">
<p>John Mahon is the Director General for Exports in the Department for International Trade.</p>

<p>John spent over 30 years in banking, working for JP Morgan and Barclays.</p>

<p>He has worked in a variety of senior roles in banking in Barclays, most recently heading Barclays Corporate Bank, providing banking services to medium and large corporations in the UK and around the world.</p>

<p>John’s previous roles include:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Head of Barclays Non Core unit, helping the bank sell and unwind businesses and assets across the investment bank, wealth and retail businesses</li>
  <li>Chief Risk Officer of the investment bank post the financial crisis</li>
  <li>Various credit trading management roles</li>
</ul>

<p>John has a BA (Mod) in Computer Science from Trinity College Dublin.  John is married with 3 children and is a dual-national Irish and UK citizen.</p>
</div>
      </section>

      <div class="current-roles" id="current-roles">
          <section class="role_appointment role" id="role_appointment_4757">
            <h1 id="director-general-exports">Director General, Exports</h1>
            <div class="govspeak">
<p>The Director General for Exports is:</p>

<ul>
  <li>responsible for leading a cross-government strategy on exports and overseas direct investment to support the UK’s underlying export potential</li>
  <li>tasked with ensuring that new and existing exporters can access the right financial, practical and promotional support to sell overseas</li>
</ul>
</div>
